Ogun State government has identified 33 public schools to pilot its modern teaching equipment and infrastructure programme in public schools in the state. The Commissioner of Education, Science and Technology, Professor Abayomi Arigbabu, made this known at the 2020-2021 annual quiz competition sponsored by SG Holdings foundation in Abeokuta. He explained that the initiative is toÂ  provide world-class teaching aids and infrastructure for the flagship schools so they can compete with foreign schools. 